data.name: labelAudited.Text
data.value:
Congratulations, your PC has now been audited - the data collected by the audit will be displayed on the Network Tab on exit from this Wizard.
Please click 'Finish' to exit this wizard or 'Next' to continue to discover and audit other PCs on your network.

data.name: labelAuditing.Text
data.value:
Your PC is now being audited. AuditWizard will collect details about your Operating System, the hardware in your PC, the applications which you have installed and details showing your Internet Explorer activity and cookies.
When the audit is complete, this information will be uploaded into the AuditWizard database.

data.name: lblProgressInfo.Text
data.value:
AuditWizard is now discovering assets on your network. Depending on the size of your network, this may take a few moments.
The following IP address range is being scanned based on your PC configuration. To change these values for future scans, select Advanced Settings from the Network Discovery tab.

data.name: lbDiscIntro.Value
data.value:
AuditWizard can discover various assets on your network including Computers, Printers and other Network Devices.

To import assets via Active Directory or discover via NetBIOS, go to the Network Discovery tab when you exit this wizard.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
AuditWizard requires a shared network folder to initiate new audits and to store audit results.
To ensure full functionality, please enter the folder path in UNC format (e.g. \\computername\\sharefolder) and enable Read/Write access for all potential user accounts.

data.name: ultraFormattedLinkLabel4.Value
data.value: It is recommended to run the service under a Domain User Account to allow the service to connect to remote PCs and control the AuditAgent service.&edsp;&edsp;Domain users will normally be specified using the format '<domain>\<user>' or '<user>@<domain>'.

data.name: ultraLabel3.Text
data.value:
Simply add a single line of text to your network logon script to audit the computer as users logon to your network.
Audits may also be performed via Email or manually via floppy disk or other removable media. Select the Audit Scanner Wizard from the Administration tab.

data.name: logonScriptLabel.Value
data.value:
You have now completed most of the steps necessary to perform an audit of your networked computers using the Network Logon Script.&edsp;&edsp;

You should now contact your System Administrator to add the command shown on the preceding page to the end of your network logon script.&edsp;&edsp;Once this has been added, the audit will be performed as your users logon to the network.

The results from the audit process will be uploaded automatically as they appear.

Please click Finish&edsp;&edsp;to exit this wizard.

data.name: agentLabel.Value
data.value:
You have now completed all of the steps required to begin auditing your networked computers using the AuditWizard Agent.

The results from the audit process will be automatically uploaded as and when they appear - if you do not see new data appearing it may be that the AuditWizard Agent has failed to either run the audit or save the results to the specified data folder.

The most likely cause of an error in the AuditWizard Agent is insufficient privilege - to identify such problems, you can view the log file for the AuditWizard Agent by selecting the computer in question in the left hand pane of the Network View and selecting View Agent Log from the ribbon.

Please click Finish to exit this wizard.
